法規內容.條文內容:
“Proof of ROC nationality” referred to in Article 5, Paragraph 1, Subparagraph 5 of the Act means any of the following documents:
1. Official printout of a ROC household registration record;
2. Personal identification card;
3. Original ROC household registration record;
4. Passport;
5. Proof of nationality;
6. Overseas Compatriot Registration Certificate;
7. Overseas Compatriot Identity Certificate;
8. Proof of ROC nationality in respect of one of the parents of the applicant, together with birth certificate of the applicant;
9. Other proof of nationality approved by the Ministry of Interior.
The Overseas Compatriot Identity Certificate mentioned in Subparagraph 7 of the previous paragraph does not include those issued to applicants who have obtained such a Certificate by providing Document of proof of Chinese ethnicity in their applications.

The following information shall be stated on an Overseas Compatriot Identity Certificate:
1. Certificate number;
2. Chinese name;
3. Foreign name and alias;
4. Date of birth;
5. Issuing authority;
6. Issue date;
7. Validity period;
8. Statement of whether Certificate application had been made on the basis of document of proof of Chinese ethnicity;
9. Other matters designated by the competent authority.
An Overseas Compatriot Identity Certificate issued for military service purposes shall also specify the personal identification card number of the applicant.
